&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dexis is a dynamic professional services firm dedicated to partnering with government and community leaders both in the U.S. and internationally to achieve critical social outcomes in a rapidly changing world.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;At Dexis, you will experience a corporate culture of inclusiveness, respect, fairness, and trust. You will be given the means and mentorship needed to succeed, and your creativity will be rewarded.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 6.75pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13.3333px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Dexis is seeking an experienced Acquisition Analyst to&amp;nbsp;support&amp;nbsp;anticipated&amp;nbsp;work with the Department of War, Office of the Undersecretary of War for Acquisition and Sustainment (OUSW(A&amp;amp;S)). The Acquisition Analyst will&amp;nbsp;lead the development of transformational acquisition proposals in support of Office of the Secretary of War (OSW) Acquisition Acceleration&amp;nbsp;Reviews (AARs).&amp;nbsp;Additionally, they&amp;nbsp;will apply deep knowledge of the Defense Acquisition System and Adaptive Acquisition Framework to research, interpret, and synthesize&amp;nbsp;Department of War (DoW)&amp;nbsp;5000-series policies into actionable, enterprise-level recommendations. The role will organize and integrate inputs from subject matter experts across government,&amp;nbsp;federally-funded&amp;nbsp;research and development centers (FFRDCs), university-affiliated research centers (UARCs),&amp;nbsp;and industry to generate a &quot;menu of ideas&quot; for senior leadership, ensuring proposals are concrete, implementation-focused, and aligned with FY26 and out-year funding opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:135,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:279}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;This position is contingent upon contract award.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:135}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
