&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dexis is a dynamic professional services firm dedicated to partnering with government and community leaders both in the U.S. and internationally to achieve critical social outcomes in a rapidly changing world.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;At Dexis, you will experience a corporate culture of inclusiveness, respect, fairness, and trust. You will be given the means and mentorship needed to succeed, and your creativity will be rewarded.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 6.75pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13.3333px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TDX – a joint-venture partnership between TI Verbatim Consulting (TIVC) and Dexis – is recruiting Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) for an anticipated requirement with the United States Special Operation Command (USSOCOM) J3-International (J3-I) Division, which will provide support to the J3-I mission, accelerate collaboration and interoperability between international Special Operations partners to more effectively deter in competition, respond in crisis, and prevail in conflict.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Directorate of Operations (J3) provides fully capable Special Operations Forces (SOF) to defend the United States and its interests and synchronizes planning of global operations against terrorist networks.&amp;nbsp; Within J3, the J3-I Division enhances interoperability, strengthens alliances, and advances partnerships across the global SOF enterprise consistent with the National Defense Strategy and Commander USSOCOM guidance and priorities.&amp;nbsp; The J3-I Division is a mixed organization consisting of US military, US government service personnel, and SOF officers and senior enlisted representatives from thirty nations (at present) from across the globe. The J3-I Division also manages USSOCOM’s network of Special Operations Liaison Officers (SOLOs) currently assigned to 22 countries worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The International Division coordinates numerous conferences throughout the year. The Division needs a highly organized and proactive individual to oversee the planning and coordination of activities for SOF Week, the SCAF Conference, and other high-profile events. This individual will serve as the primary leader responsible for managing all logistical, operational, and collaborative efforts to ensure the successful execution of these critical events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based in Tampa, Florida, is contingent upon contract award, and requires an active Top Secret clearance with SCI eligibility.&lt;/p&gt;
